# TODO.6 — VLM Scene Extraction + OCR Node

## Objective

Implement `src/vlm_extract.py` — use a vision-language model to extract scene descriptions and OCR from sampled frames.

## Tasks

1. Implement `run(frames: list[SampledFrame], config: JobConfig) -> list[VisualEvent]`:
   - Load VLM (default: Qwen3-VL-4B-Instruct via Transformers)
   - For each frame (or batch of nearby frames), prompt the model to output structured JSON:
     - scene description
     - people present
     - actions observed
     - objects visible
     - visible text (OCR) with bounding boxes and confidence
     - term candidates relevant to the topic
   - Parse JSON output, validate against VisualEvent schema
   - Group frames within the same time window into a single VisualEvent
2. Design the VLM prompt template (structured JSON output, topic-aware)
3. Write `tests/test_vlm_extract.py`:
   - Mock model inference
   - Test JSON parsing and validation
   - Test frame grouping logic
   - Test error handling for malformed model output

## Acceptance Criteria

- Each VisualEvent has all required fields populated
- Frames within 2s of each other merged into one event
- Malformed model output handled gracefully (logged, not crashed)
- Tests pass without GPU or model weights

## Dependencies

- TODO.1, TODO.5

## Notes

- Phase 1 uses a single VLM for both scene description and OCR
- Phase 2 will add PaddleOCR-VL as a separate dedicated OCR node
- VLM prompt should instruct the model to output JSON only, no free-form text
